rs: Nina Rimsky, Nick Gabrieli, et al.\n   - Year: 2023\n   - arXiv: 2312.06681\n   - Why relevant: Foundational work on activation steering via contrastive pairs.\n\n7. [Identifying and Manipulating Personality Traits in LLMs Through Activation Engineering](2412.10427v2_identifying_and_manipulating_personality_traits_in.pdf)\n   - Authors: Rumi A. Allbert, James K. Wiles\n   - Year: 2024\n   - arXiv: 2412.10427\n   - Why relevant: Early work on activation-based personality modification.\n\n8. [Bias Runs Deep: Implicit Reasoning Biases in Persona-Assigned LLMs](2311.04892v2_bias_runs_deep_implicit_reasoning_biases_in_person.pdf)\n   - Authors: Shashank Gupta, Vaishnavi Shrivastava, et al.\n   - Year: 2023\n   - arXiv: 2311.04892\n   - Why relevant: Explores how persona adoption surfaces deep-seated biases in LLMs.\n"}}
